            "commit": "abd8c6dd6fa708e8064f1095350eba23b9437b7c",
            "subject": "LU-2791 ldlm: release reference against failed lock"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Emoly Liu",
          "email": "emoly.liu@intel.com",
          "date": "2013-03-13 15:51:37.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Emoly Liu",
          "email": "emoly.liu@intel.com",
          "date": "2013-03-13 15:51:37.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "LU-2871 lod: stripe data across the OSTs correctly",
        "message": "LU-2871 lod: stripe data across the OSTs correctly\n\nSince the ost-in-use array is initialized with 0 and isn't set with\nOST index number correctly, OST0 is always skipped when allocating\nobjects on OSTs with specific stripe offset (offset > 0).\n\nFor example, when running command \"lfs setstripe -c -1 -i 2 testfile\"\non 4 OSTs, we will get a wrong layout, like\n        obdidx           objid           objid           group\n             2               3            0x3                0\n             3               3            0x3                0\n             1               4            0x4                0\n             2               4            0x4                0\n\nTo fix the problem, we initialize the array with -1 instead, and store\nthe correct OST index number in it.\n\nSigned-off-by: Liu Ying <emoly.liu@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I5eeced6b66ae40771f8896204c5a6ed8e6663e57\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
